01:18.140 --> 01:19.207
Hey, I'm downstairs.

01:19.275 --> 01:21.009
Can you come down here? It's an emergency.

01:33.789 --> 01:35.056
I want to talk.

01:35.124 --> 01:36.858
I have to talk to you about Adrian.

01:36.926 --> 01:39.127
What? That's the emergency?

01:39.195 --> 01:41.696
My dad told her dad that she's pregnant.

01:41.764 --> 01:42.897
And her mother got home last night,

01:42.965 --> 01:44.699
so I know they're all gonna be talking about it.

01:44.767 --> 01:45.934
Not at 5:00 in the morning.

01:46.002 --> 01:47.035
What are you doing here?

01:47.103 --> 01:48.670
You said if I needed to talk...

01:48.738 --> 01:50.238
Why didn't you come up?

01:50.306 --> 01:52.874
Because I don't know who you're with these days,

01:52.942 --> 01:53.875
if you're with anyone.

01:53.943 --> 01:55.710
I'm not, so talk.

01:55.778 --> 01:58.113
Two minutes ago I was asleep, so I
don't know how much help I can be.

01:58.180 --> 02:00.248
Okay. Here's the thing.

02:00.316 --> 02:02.550
I'm in a classic no-win situation.

02:02.618 --> 02:04.653
If Adrian has the baby, that's not good.

02:04.720 --> 02:07.022
If Adrian doesn't have the
baby, that's even horrible.

02:07.089 --> 02:08.990
And I have to take Amy to the airport,

02:09.058 --> 02:12.460
which is a classic no-win situation with a twist,

02:12.528 --> 02:15.096
now that I think about it. Don't think about it.

02:15.164 --> 02:16.698
If I don't talk about this...

02:16.766 --> 02:18.667
and get my head straightened
out, I'm gonna implode.

02:18.734 --> 02:20.802
Or is it explode? Wait. What is it?

02:20.870 --> 02:22.370
I don't know.

02:22.438 --> 02:25.006
But you're already a mess,
whether you implode or explode.

02:25.074 --> 02:26.574
Do you want Adrian to have the baby?

02:26.642 --> 02:28.009
I don't. No.

02:28.077 --> 02:29.711
I don't want her to go through with this.

02:29.779 --> 02:32.247
I mean, what are we gonna do with a baby?

02:32.314 --> 02:36.785
And if we have a baby, Amy and I are
never gonna be able to get back together.

02:36.852 --> 02:38.787
That's not a good enough
reason not to have the baby.

02:38.854 --> 02:41.990
You and Amy might not stay together baby or not.

02:42.058 --> 02:44.793
No, because she's gonna find
out that Adrian is pregnant...

02:44.860 --> 02:46.528
or that she terminated the pregnancy,

02:46.595 --> 02:47.696
and either way I lose,

02:47.763 --> 02:50.031
hence again, the classic no-win situation.

02:50.099 --> 02:51.766
Have you talked to Adrian?

02:51.834 --> 02:53.635
I tried. She doesn't want to talk.

02:53.703 --> 02:56.204
She's been pushing me away, putting
it off until her mother gets back...

02:56.272 --> 02:57.672
so that she can talk to her.

02:57.740 --> 02:59.307
I'm sure they're talking about abortion.

02:59.375 --> 03:00.875
I don't want an abortion,

03:00.943 --> 03:02.877
but I don't want a baby, hence, again, the...

03:02.945 --> 03:05.013
Don't say it. What do I do?

03:06.182 --> 03:07.582
I mean, what do I do?

03:07.650 --> 03:09.651
I've been talking to my
dad. I'm talking to you now.

03:09.719 --> 03:11.086
I've been talking to myself for days,

03:11.153 --> 03:12.353
and still I don't know what to do,

03:12.421 --> 03:13.722
or if there really is anything to do,

03:13.789 --> 03:16.725
other than do what Adrian
says and just stay out of it.

03:16.792 --> 03:18.760
But if I stay out of it... You're on a loop now.

03:18.828 --> 03:20.528
You're like a cartoon character chasing his tail,

03:20.596 --> 03:22.030
spinning around until he burrows himself...

03:22.098 --> 03:23.298
into the center of the earth.

03:23.365 --> 03:25.533
Stop. What cartoon character?

03:25.601 --> 03:26.768
I don't know.

03:26.836 --> 03:28.670
Ben, I can't decide this for you.

03:28.738 --> 03:30.071
You can't even decide this for you.

03:30.139 --> 03:32.307
You're gonna have to let Adrian decide this.

03:32.374 --> 03:35.643
And whatever she decides, you go along with her.

03:35.711 --> 03:37.879
If I know Adrian, she's not gonna have a baby.

03:37.947 --> 03:38.880
That's just the thing.

03:38.948 --> 03:40.348
Maybe I should go over there...

03:40.416 --> 03:41.950
and try to talk her out of not having the baby.

03:42.017 --> 03:45.453
But then if I do that, then I have a baby.

03:45.521 --> 03:47.021
You're still spinning.

03:47.089 --> 03:48.056
Look, there's nothing you can do.

03:48.124 --> 03:49.390
Stay out of it.

03:49.458 --> 03:51.526
My dad told me to get involved.

03:51.594 --> 03:54.462
Oh, then do what he said, and leave me out of it.

03:54.530 --> 03:56.064
You said I could talk to you.

03:56.132 --> 03:58.633
Talk to me after the decision's been made.

03:58.701 --> 04:00.235
This sucks.

04:00.302 --> 04:04.105
Hey, what's going on?

04:06.542 --> 04:07.542
Will you ever learn?

04:09.979 --> 04:11.179
Will I?

04:18.120 --> 04:19.788
What was that?

04:19.855 --> 04:22.590
That was a guy in a no-win situation.

04:22.658 --> 04:25.360
Ben Boykewich in a no-win situation?

04:26.762 --> 04:28.730
What could that be?

04:28.798 --> 04:30.632
What can't Ben Boykewich buy his way out of?

04:30.699 --> 04:32.233
Come on, it's freezing down here.

04:32.301 --> 04:34.002
Let's go back to bed.

04:34.069 --> 04:35.436
Tell me.

04:35.504 --> 04:37.372
It's nothing.

04:37.439 --> 04:39.440
You ever done it in a butcher shop?

04:40.843 --> 04:42.710
There are security cameras.

04:44.380 --> 04:45.446
That could be fun.

04:45.514 --> 04:47.448
Back upstairs.

04:52.955 --> 04:55.256
<i>...</i>

05:03.866 --> 05:05.834
<i>...</i>

05:05.835 --> 05:10.835
